OL,3,CSir Lindsay Hoyle: 'People should
OL,4,Cdecide if Jersey gets elected Speaker'
OL,6,FThe people of Jersey should decide
OL,7,Fwhether to have an elected Speaker,
OL,8,FSir Lindsay Hoyle has said.
OL,10,FHe made the comments to ITV News
OL,11,Fduring his first visit to the island
OL,12,Fto mark Sir Timothy Le Cocq's
OL,13,Fretirement as Bailiff.
OL,15,FJersey's current constitutional set-up
OL,16,Fsees the Bailiff appointed by the King
OL,17,Fto serve as its Chief Justice and
OL,18,Fpreside over the island's Parliament,
OL,19,Fthe States Assembly.
