OL,3,CSir Lindsay Hoyle: 'People should
OL,4,Cdecide if Jersey gets elected Speaker'
OL,6,FWhen Sir Lindsay, the Speaker of the
OL,7,FHouse of Commons, was asked about the
OL,8,Fissue, he said: "People always tempt
OL,9,Fme with the question, 'Should they
OL,10,Fhave an elected speaker?'.
OL,12,F"It's not for me, it's for the people
OL,13,Fof Jersey to decide. I always respect
OL,14,Fthe views of the people.
OL,16,F"I come to parliaments, I visit
OL,17,Fdifferent jurisdictions, I respect
OL,18,Fwhat they wish to have. It's not for
OL,19,Fme to decide or impose, it's for me to
OL,20,Flisten.
