OL,3,CSir Lindsay Hoyle: 'People should
OL,4,Cdecide if Jersey gets elected Speaker'
OL,6,F"If the people say they want an
OL,7,Felected Speaker, so be it; if they
OL,8,Fdon't, they don't."
OL,10,FJersey's External Relations Minister,
OL,11,FDeputy Ian Gorst, adds:
OL,12,F"Theoretically, I've supported the
OL,13,Fseparation of the role in Jersey but
OL,14,Fpractically, the Standing Orders
OL,15,Fdetermine what happens in the States
OL,16,Fto a much greater extent than they do
OL,17,Fin the UK Parliament.
