OL,3,CSir Lindsay Hoyle: 'People should
OL,4,Cdecide if Jersey gets elected Speaker'
OL,6,F"For example, States Members decide at
OL,7,Fthe end of every sitting the order of
OL,8,Fbusiness and what will be on the
OL,9,Fagenda for the following sitting.
OL,11,F"All speakers get called to speak in
OL,12,Fall debates, unlike in the UK, so the
OL,13,Frole of the Bailiff is really ensuring
OL,14,Fthat our Parliament acts within
OL,15,FStanding Orders and that actually is
OL,16,Fquite different to some of the powers
OL,17,Fthat the Speaker in the UK has."
